Today marks 14 years since your departure from this world. Time has a way of making your absence feel easier, but not a day goes by that I don’t feel you in everything I do. I think the biggest reason I continue in music is because it opens the most direct line to you. I miss our jams, deep conversations, and our plans for the future. You still remain the kindest, classiest, focused, and most exemplary man I’ll ever know and I thank you for leaving even a microscopic spec of these qualities in me. I love you dad.

Starting 2023 right. Tune in to @goodmorningamerica at 8:50 am today.

March 17th, 2023. It’s St. Patrick’s Day and I’m a whole Spanish book away from being Irish, but I sure am the luckiest man alive to have asked @jennystrote to be my girlfriend 3 years ago today. Every day is filled with laughter, our dreams grow bigger (and so do our cats), and our love always feels new. You keep me grounded, remind me of what’s most important, and make me look forward to coming back home to our movie marathons, trip planning, and our daily routine. Above all, you have the kindest heart, are absolutely beautiful and sexy inside and out, are driven and productive in everything you put yourself to, and make everything make sense when things feels blurry.
.
Loving you is a treat I want to cherish forever. Happy anniversary, baby. Thank you for loving me ❤️
